{
  "texts": [
    "Related studies have analyzed voluntary ad archives to uncover transparency gaps [33,140].",
    "While to examine platform policy evolutions after Article 27 (Code: RA), text analysis can track changes in community standards and terms of service on mis/disinformation before vs after DSA implementation.",
    "Semantic modeling can detect subtle policy shifts across platforms over time, as witnessed by similar work analyzing platforms' policy dynamics around emerging speech issues [118,143].Independent Audit Studies Audit studies 6 enable causal assessment of DSA impacts by directly testing platform responses through carefully controlled researcher-instigated interventions [87,172].",
    "Computational tools allow efficient large-scale auditing of critical areas like ad transparency, fake accounts and disinformation detection [88].To assess impacts of diligence obligations (Code: DD), researcher-instigated audit studies can systematically post synthetic disinformation from control vs treatment groups, and compare detection and removal rates based on platform size and due diligence status.",
    "Factorial experimental designs can isolate impacts of specific obligations."
  ]
}